misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that there will always be at least one student, so it is always safe to use `numberOfStudents - 1` as a valid index and read `names[index]` / `scores[index]` without checking for `N == 0`.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, arrays can have length 0, and `numberOfStudents - 1` becomes `-1` when `numberOfStudents` is 0. Indexing with `-1` causes an `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException`. A correct execution model must account for boundary cases before indexing arrays.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Runtime exception (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException) if the user enters 0 for `N`. Otherwise, output is correct.
